Condition: What is the effect on herring?

B: The herring are members of the small pelagics group, so the increased harveting effort resulted in more herring being killed.

Condition: What is the effect on winter flounder?

B: The winter flounder are members of the flatfish group, so decreasing harvesting efforts resulted in their increased biomass.

Condition: What is the effect on yellowtail flounder?

B: Despite the decreased harvesting efforts for Flatfish, the yellowtail flounder has increased competition with the Winter Flounder, resulting in an unsubstantial increase.

Condition: What is the effect on skates?

B: Due to the increased harvesting efforts on Elasmobranchs, the Skates suffered losses in their biomass beause they belong to the Elasmobranch group.

Condition: What is the effect on cod?

B: The spicy dogfish, an Elasmobranch, predate the Cod, so a decrease in the Dogfish biomass indicated an increase in Cod.

Condition: What is the effect on haddock?

B: The haddock have no particular relationship with any of the elasmobranch fish, therefore their biomass was unaffected.

Condition: What is the effect on windowpane?

B: The windowpane compete with the skates, a member of the elasmabranch group. Therefore, a decrease in Skates indicated a small decrease in windowpane.
